# Working Agreement — Quick Reference

Full version: [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md). Read it.

## Before You Change Anything

- Check [docs/open-questions.md](mdc:docs/open-questions.md). Don't silently resolve open items — ask the user.
- Look for a relevant skill in `~/.cursor/skills-cursor/` before reinventing.

## When You Change Anything

Update docs **in the same change set** when you touch:

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| Tech stack / hosting / routing / PWA | `docs/architecture.md` |
| Firestore or JSON shapes | `docs/data-model.md` (bump `schemaVersion`) |
| User-visible feature behavior | `docs/features/<name>.md` |
| Colors / typography / spacing | `docs/design/theme.md` |
| Patterns for future growth | `docs/extensibility.md` |
| Resolved open question | remove from `docs/open-questions.md`, fold into the relevant doc |
| New doc file | link it from `docs/README.md` and root `README.md` |

## Defaults to Honor

- **Mobile-first PWA, Android primary.** No iOS-only work unless free. Touch targets ≥ 48 dp, no hover-only UI, `100dvh` not `100vh`, respect `env(safe-area-inset-*)`. Lock portrait.
- **Default language: Ukrainian (uk).** All user-visible strings via i18n bundle — never inline.
- **Multi-user-ready.** Data under `/users/{uid}/...`. Whitelist is a Firestore collection (`/allowedUsers/{email}`). Never hardcode an identity.
- **TypeScript strict.** Prefer discriminated unions over boolean flags.
- **Single-owner whitelist enforcement** stays in Firestore rules — never weaken for "dev". Use the emulator.

## Token-Efficient Workflow

- Delegate bulk edits / boilerplate / mechanical refactors to a `composer-2.5-fast` subagent via the `Task` tool.
- Reserve the expensive model for architecture decisions, debugging, and review.
- Verify subagent output by reading **only changed files** + `npm run typecheck`/`lint`.
- Batch independent tool calls in one message. Use `Grep`/`Glob` before `Read`.
- For research-only questions, use `readonly: true` on `Task`.

See [AGENTS.md §8](mdc:AGENTS.md) for the prompt template.

## Red Flags — Stop and Ask

- Schema change without a `schemaVersion` bump.
- New feature without a `docs/features/*.md` entry.
- Hardcoded owner email or single-user assumption in code.
- Inlined user-visible string (not via i18n).
- "Temporary" auth bypass.
- New heavyweight dependency added without justification.
